Three Saturday’s in a row I have received awful customer service at this location. On one occasion I placed my drink order and requested “light oat milk” and was given a drink with regular amount oat milk. In order to not make a huge fuss instead of asking them to remake my drink I asked them to just dump some of it and add more coffee. When they dumped part of my iced drink they also dumped most of the ice with it as well as the added sweetener. They returned my drink with the added coffee but hardly any ice and the proportions of the sweetener were off. I took a sip and my drink was not good. I went back to the bar to ask for a cup of ice and a couple of stevias and the barista told me that I had to request those items when I place my order at the register. I tried to explain to him that my drink was made incorrectly and I was trying to adjust my portions but he kept talking over me telling me “it’s fine this time but next time request this when you place your order” and waving me away. All I really wanted when I walked into this location was a nice cold iced hazelnut coffee with light oat milk after my morning run and I left with a horrible drink that I ended up dumping.  Today, I walked in and requested my drink with “light oat milk” and I asked the person at register to please make sure she noted light oat milk because I had an issue the previous two weeks with my drink. She said “of course no problem” and proceeded to tell the barista that my drink was to be made with light oat milk. When I received my drink it had a regular portion of oat milk. I proceeded to tell the barista that I requested light oat milk. She looked at the sticker on the drink and said “well it doesn’t say light on the sticker” then the other barista turned to her and said “she requested light oat milk I’ll remake it”. The original barista rolled her eyes and just took the drink back poured some out and returned it and looked at me and said “is this better?” I responded “uhhh not really” she huffed snatched the drink poured more out added more coffee to the same cup and returned my drink with coffee running all down the sides of my cup and walked away. This is not the first time I get “it didn’t say light oat milk on the sticker” from this barista in particular. I honestly, do not understand why I should be putting up with this awful customer service from these two baristas. I placed my order in a respectful way and I expect my drink to be made as requested and as a patron I expect to be treated with respect. There is no need for the rude customer service. I have been a customer at this location for the past 15 years have met and interacted with many baristas at this location and never have I ever been treated as rudely as I was in the last few weeks at this location. I’m so disappointed.
